    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Dutch style characterized by construction as the basis for the form of an object, with ornament also playing an important role. It is characterized by the use of rare and expensive materials, the mixing of many stylistic elements, and much ornament. This style flourished in Amsterdam. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
